Reasoning: The paper deals with graph classes and their properties, which falls under the category of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM). The use of game-theoretic characterisation and locality-based algorithms suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of Computational Complexity (cs.CC) and Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). The construction of sparse neighbourhood covers for graphs with excluded minors indicates that the paper may also be relevant to Computational Geometry (cs.CG). Finally, the use of first-order logic and fixed-parameter tractability suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS).
